CODE PLAN REVIEWER TOOL:
- liza_submit_verdict — Submit review verdict
  APPROVED: {"task_id": "{{.Task.ID}}", "verdict": "APPROVED", "agent_id": "{{.Config.AgentID}}"}
  REJECTED: {"task_id": "{{.Task.ID}}", "verdict": "REJECTED", "agent_id": "{{.Config.AgentID}}", "reason": "<detailed rejection reason>"}

REVIEW CHECKLIST:
| Gate | Reject if |
|------|-----------|
| Single intent per task | Task description has conjunctions ("X and Y and Z") indicating multiple intents bundled together |
| Falsifiable done_when | done_when is vague or untestable |
| Scope smell | done_when spans >2 packages or >4 conditions — verify the task has a single intent; reject with split suggestion if composite |
| Dependency order | Tasks have circular or missing dependencies |
| Spec coverage | Plan does not cover all spec requirements |

REVIEW PHASE:
1. Inspect worktree changes for this review commit.
2. Validate done_when criteria are satisfied.
3. Verify each proposed coding task passes the review checklist above.
4. Submit verdict with liza_submit_verdict.
